        <key_statement>
            <statement_id>1</statement_id>
            <statement>Plants terrestrial or on logs or tree bases; segments at base of blade
                gradually reduced to auricles; petiole scales threadlike and inconspicuous or
                absent; veins 2–3-forked. 1a. Pecluma ptilodon var. caespitosa</statement>
